{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb85ecb09-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s5374"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5374"},"text":"§ 5374.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Miscellaneous positions in the executive branch","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The head of the agency concerned shall fix the annual rate of basic pay for each position in the executive branch specifically referred to in, or covered by, a conforming change in statute made by section 305 of the Government Employees Salary Reform Act of 1964 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/422"},"text":"78 Stat. 422","children":[],"tail":"), or other position in the executive branch for which the annual pay is fixed at a rate of $18,500 or more under special provision of statute enacted before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-08-14"},"text":"August 14, 1964","children":[],"tail":", which is not placed in a level of the Executive Schedule set forth in subchapter II of this chapter, at a rate equal to the pay rate of a grade and step of the General Schedule set forth in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5332"},"text":"section 5332 of this title","children":[],"tail":". The head of the agency concerned shall report each action taken under this section to the Office of Personnel Management and publish a notice thereof in the Federal Register, except when the President determines that the report and publication would be contrary to the interest of national security."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb85ecb0a-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/554"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–554","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/473"},"text":"80 Stat. 473","children":[],"tail":", § 5364; renumbered § 5374 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/454/tVIII/s801/a/3/A/ii"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–454, title VIII, § 801(a)(3)(A)(ii)","children":[],"tail":", title IX, § 906(a)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/1221"},"text":"92 Stat. 1221","children":[],"tail":", 1224.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb85ecb0b-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb85ecb0c-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idb85ecb0d-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Derivation","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"U.S. Code","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"